        overview1: "Foreign investors in Saudi Arabia who suffer losses as a result of unlawful government action, expropriation, or the breach of investment agreements have legal rights to compensation — under Saudi domestic law, applicable bilateral investment treaties, and general principles of international investment law. Pursuing investor compensation requires specialist expertise in the applicable legal framework, the quantification of investment losses, and the selection and management of the appropriate legal proceedings. Qanoni has pursued compensation claims for foreign investors for over 30 years — combining domestic Saudi law expertise with international investment law knowledge to maximise recovery. Our online consultation means specialist advice is available immediately.",
