        overview1: "Winning a court judgment is only half the battle — the other half is enforcing it. Saudi Arabia's dedicated enforcement courts, established under the Saudi Enforcement Law (Royal Decree M/53 of 2012), provide a powerful and specialist framework for the enforcement of domestic and foreign court judgments. The Saudi enforcement courts have wide powers — including bank account garnishment, real estate attachment, travel bans, and other coercive measures — to compel payment from judgment debtors. Qanoni has over 30 years of experience enforcing court judgments before Saudi enforcement courts, acting urgently to secure debtors' assets and pursue every available enforcement tool until full recovery is achieved.",
