        overview1: "Commercial arbitration has rapidly become the preferred method for resolving significant business disputes in Saudi Arabia — offering a faster, more confidential, and more commercially sophisticated alternative to court litigation. The Saudi Centre for Commercial Arbitration (SCCA) provides an internationally recognised institutional framework governed by the Saudi Arbitration Law (Royal Decree M/34 of 2012), which aligns closely with the UNCITRAL Model Law and ensures that Saudi arbitral awards are enforceable domestically and internationally. Qanoni has represented clients in commercial arbitration proceedings for over 30 years — across construction, commercial contracts, joint ventures, banking, insurance, real estate, and corporate disputes — with a track record of delivering effective representation at every stage of the arbitration process.",
